    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="685"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 P.W./10–845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Political Adviser in Japan</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-08">October 8,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received October 11—12:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. It would be helpful to this office if we could be furnished by telegraph with
                    a list, as so far compiled, of suspected Japanese war criminals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
